title.narrative: Integrated Resilience Programme in Haiti - Monitoring and Evaluation

description.narrative: This activity (Integrated Resilience Programme in Haiti - Monitoring and Evaluation) is a component of Integrated Resilience Programme in Haiti reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Humanitarian assistance' and a budget of £764,861. This component benefits Haiti, and works in the following sector(s): Disaster prevention and preparedness. , with the following implementing partners: Crown Agents Limited. The start date is 01-09-2014 and the end date is 31-12-2016.
